- Add ability to bulk remove users
- you should be able to search for a group of users using the existing parameters in the Manage Users screen and bulk remove matching users
- this can assist in removing spam accounts on public wikis that allow public signups

Not really sure if this is a bug or not....

Paste the following text into "Wiki Markup" for a new page:

{code}
kma> /Library/Application\ Support/Net-Print/bin/lpr -A -Pk-ccc1@page4 test.ps
{code}

Click the "Preview" tab, and you will see:

kma> /Library/Application\ Support/Net-Print/bin/lpr -A -Pk-ccc1@page4 test.ps

Click the "Rich Text" tab, then click the "Preview" tab, and you will see:

kma> /Library/Application\ Support/Net-Print/bin/lpr \-A \-Pk-ccc1@page4 test.ps

Click the "Wiki Markup" tab, and you will see:

{code}
kma> /Library/Application\ Support/Net-Print/bin/lpr \-A \-Pk-ccc1@page4 test.ps
{code}

