At the moment, redeploying Confluence inside any web container has problems. 

We have noticed in one past customer case, where multiple redeployments of Confluence caused more and more JAVA heap to be permanently consumed until the whole instance crashes with an OutOfMemory error. This appears to be caused by a resource leak related to the JVM not being able to collect on the heap consumed by classloaders. This needs further investigation.

